result.execSummary:
The defendant Synjin S. Jenks was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Operating While Revoked (Rev due to alc/contr subst/refusal), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 343.44(1)(b).
  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Costs to be paid directly to the Waushara County Clerk of Court within 60 days or establish a payment plan.  Failure to pay may result in suspension of your driver's license, tax intercept, a civil judgment being entered against you, a warrant being issued for your arrest for contempt and/or the debt being turned over to a collection agency.
Time served sentence with application of prior time served and Good Time credit.
Any uncharged referral for possession of paraphernalia with an offense date of 02/28/2015 is also dismissed and read-in.

records.addlTxt: Case Called @ 2:28 PM: Defendant Synjin S. Jenks in court with attorney Ben Szilagyi.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin.    Complaint Stated - Advised of offense and minimum/maximum penalty.  Receipt Admitted - Reading waived.  Per DA:  Resolution recited - pending charges remain.  SPD and Def concur w/recital.    Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed.  Plea Ct No 1 (OAR):  NC  Plea Ct No 2 (Obst):  NC  Court accepts pleas and enters JOC.  Ct Nos 3 and 4 both DRI.  Court will also dismiss and read in any uncharged referral for poss of minor para with an offense date of 2/28/2015.  Statement by Def: None offered.  The Court:  Accepts recommendation of counsel and imposes 41 days WCJ as to each count - concurrent terms - GT and time served sentence with credit for 31 days.  Court Costs plus DNA Surcharge as to each count.  Appeal Rights Given.

The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing or ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician.

Case Called @ 1:10 pm: Defendant Synjin S. Jenks in court, in custody, with attorney Ben Szilagyi both appearing via video.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin.    Complaint Stated - Advised of offense and minimum/maximum penalty.  Receipt Admitted - Reading waived.  Per SPD - eligibility confirmed.  Per DA:  States it is believed there may also be a companion charge of OWI 2. Argues for $1500 cash bond w/conditions and also states pending Waupaca Co charges for the record.  SPD argues for Signature Bond or perhaps lower cash bond.  DA clarifies and states that more than likely no further charging as to OWI will be forthcoming.  The Court orders Bond of $1500 cash w/conditions.  IA Scheduled - NOH Given.  Riverside Ruling in favor of the State.  Initial appearance scheduled for March 30, 2015 at 03:00 pm.
